reviews.review_text: Fresh Ideas Start Here sells fresh and frozen sustainably caught seafood and the majority of their products are locally sourced. They have seafood that is raw and ready to cook as well as foods that have already been assembled and may just need a bit of time in the oven or on the stove before its ready to eat. (eg. Crab Cakes,Truffle Spot Prawn Mac n Cheese) To celebrate the launch of their fall seasonal menu, Fresh Ideas Start Here was offering a small bowl of complimentary seafood congee to the first 50 customers who came into their store and mentioned the word halibut. Wed never tried this seafood congee before, but apparently its a cult favourite so we went to the store right when it opened and managed to bring home some of this famed seafood congee. Oh wow! This seafood congee exceeded my expectations. I totally understand now why its a cult favourite. It was packed with seafood. They dont skimp on ingredients at this place. According to the stickers stuck onto our containers, a small congee is normally $6 and a large congee is normally $8. I would absolutely go back and pay to have this seafood congee again! Im so happy that its Fall now. With hot summer days leaving, and cooler weather arriving, we should definitely have a reason to go back for the seafood congee! Service: Good Parking: Plentiful and free Location: 7515 Market Crossing #180, Burnaby
Chris is always friendly and the seafood is super fresh and their prices are great. I grab stuff to make dinner and ceviche and stuff all the time! Highly recommend

The employees are very kind and explains in detail if you have any questions. I visited because I wanted to get sea urchin(uni) and spotted prawn, but it was not the season yet, so I bought frozen sea urchin and defrosted it. Also I m very satisfied with the poke that the staff makes on the spot and it was delicious. I m going to visit here again.
I come here to buy uni. The staff here is amazing. Very knowledgeable and always cheerful. You leave with a smile on your face. I recommend that you also try their smoke salmon and cod.
Popped in today and all we got was ready made food--onigiri, inari, and a poke bowl. All were very fresh and tasty and the staff were very good to us :) Will be back!

If youre in the area or not.  Craving for some fresh poke!!  Look no further!  You can purchase the onigiri here as well to go with your poke bowl.  Its jam packed full of fresh poke and ingredients.  Need some super fresh seafood as well!   They have all that as well.  Cant be any fresher then them processing it in the store.  They do have some frozen products as well, but mainly fresh.  You wont be disappointed

Best Poke bowl I have ever tried. My sister and I both got the Bara Chirashi and it was delicious! They ran out of octopus so we picked more ahi tuna. I may decide to do the same substitute in future since the tuna was great!

Ive had this place on my radar for months, finally got a chance to order online and pick up! Their seafood congee was A++ and was apparently on special ($8, regular $10). It was packed full of seafood and so comforting! There were a few shells/bones throughout, but it was so delicious and bountiful with ingredients, we didnt mind. Just checked their site and doesnt look like its offered anymore, which would be shame, would have definitely come back for the congee alone! Also had 3 customized regular poke bowls, no complaints. The fish was so fresh and we enjoyed some of their more unique toppings, like the ginger-y squid salad. Great sauces to compliment the fish! I snagged a couple of their onigiri left from the grab-and-go section, also fair in size with a mildly spicy cooked tuna flavour. Perfect for a snack or lunch/dinner accompaniment. I picked up some frozen soup that Im excited to try, and cant wait to be back for more poke!

Poke bar is fresh and tasty. Delivery is a great option too. We just tried the Valentines Day platter (medium) and it was fantastic! The crab dip and crab cakes are amazing too! Ive been going to F.I.S.H. for years and they dont disappoint.
This little store has a great selection of seafood. Super friendly staff and I especially enjoy their salmon jerky - depending on flavour and fish, the jerkies range from $6 - $12 per 100g.
I go here every year for spot prawn season! Always fresh and live. They do pre-orders online too and sell a bunch of other amazing seafood in-store (check out the uni or uni pasta).

Great quality seafood products, very good service. Especially their manager Jordan, he is very knowledgeable, helpful,  shares tips and recipes. He goes above and beyond to accommodate special requests.
Great place to grab UNI. They are around the same price as T&T but more fresh (as writing this review). Will come back for Seafood.
Fresh uni! Friendly staff.
Bought frozen Hokkaido Scallops and sashimi grade salmon and tuna. It was amazing! The store was clean and the employees were super friendly! Thanks guys, so glad you re my local go to for good fish!
Ordered the caviar set - Great value and price! Staff are super friendly and helpful. We also starting purchasing fresh seafood here.
A hidden gem for seafood lovers. Their congee is so nice and filled so much seafood. The owners and workers are amazingly friendly, always giving extras for free.

They are so knowledgeable, so friendly, and patient. I really appreciate his they take the time to sort out my mussels and clams to make sure theyre fresh. I asked many questions, they helped me choose what I needed to impress my mother in law. I always order online through them. I like the different methods of payment available online. Honestly its always a positive experience coming here. I also look forward to their freezer sales.

Very friendly staff, I would highly recommend coming here if you want something fresh to go. Prices vary but I feel like its definitely worth it! They also have a poke bar, the rice isn t the greatest imo and I personally probably would ve went with a salad base if I knew but the toppings were great regardless! Easy to access area, located in market crossing. Lots of parking space, lots of things on display as well.

My daughter always requests poke bowls from here. Always fresh. Great service with a smile. They pack the food into the bowls so you feel you are getting great value. I love how you can add ikura or uni to your order because you feel like splurging. Great little gem in Burnaby.
best value and quality poke. the fish is always so fresh because it is also a fish market. our favorite poke place.
Delicious prepped meals, fresh seafood, and friendly service.

I love going to shop at this place for all of my seafood needs. They always have a good selection of fish that is local and very well priced. I always get the crab and artichoke dip and the taste of it is very good.  Overall very and helpful staff, good seafood at great prices and the taste of everything is great. Highly recommend to all

So my wife and I came here a few times to get fresh seafood, and yeah its a great place to get seafood.  One time, when we were shopping here, we tried their seafood congee.  Holy $#!% was it good!  We got two orders the next time we went back.  Now every time we pass the market crossing area, we stop at FISH and get their congee and happen to get some fresh seafood. But the main objective now is the congee. Order large.

Best price for fresh sea urchin in lower mainland. Great service. N for the Chinese style cold cooked crab, just have to give them a 1 to 2 day advanced order for that. Instead of going 80km out of my way from surrey to deep cove thru horrible traffic for the alternative

I love this place. Poke and congee bar in the back with great quality seafood, naturally. Excellent prices- $11 poke bowl I think. Nice selection of fish, great scallops, oysters, and their assorted fish cakes are always good. Lots of interesting bits in the freezer - DIY chirashi sets, soups, lox trim, sashimi, spot prawns. My go to seafood place and absolutely the only place in the area worth discussing.

I was referred to this place by a friend. I was pleasantly surprised by their products. The poke bar is situated at the end of the store. Generous portions. Great menu selection. Delicious and very affordable. Very nice and friendly staff. Truly this place is very underrated.

BEST FISHMONGER! I may not live in Burnaby but I come out here for consistently good quality seafood.  The staff are friendly and helpful.  There will always be local choices whether they be fresh or frozen.  Ive had fresh and frozen and it is both good.  Especially the sashimi grade selection and shell fish.
Great local product / selections, always fresh with knowledgeable staff. Forgot my wallet there today, they secured it and held until I could pick it up. Trustworthy, good people.

Love F.I.S.H.!!! Its my go-to place for fresh seafood. They are always super friendly and helpful; answering any questions I may have. Their seafood is top notch and pricing is super fair. Keep an eye out for their biannual freezer stock-up sales!! They always have seasonal items too (like spot prawns, local BC uni). Wouldnt consider going elsewhere for seafood and is the only place I trust for fresh seafood!

Just bought some fresh green uni trays from here and will be returning for more! The quality of all their products are top notch and so is their service. Highly recommend for anyone who loves their seafood.
Lots of options for seafood. Crab cakes, fresh scallops, mussels, live crab...They even had the Japanese Kewpie mayo.

I almost dont want to write a review for this business because it is SO GOOD...but more people are finding out about it (when I go in sometimes there are lined ups) - so here goes. I love seafood. LOVE IT. Love it so much I l drive down to Stevenston and buy fresh of the boat. BUT, I dont have the time to do that so often. However, I do go into Fresh Ideas Start Here  at least once a week to pick up something fresh. Last week it was fresh, wild pink salmon and it was amazing. They were super busy for Valentines Day but very prepared. I could not believe the amount of people coming in to pick up live lobsters and crabs. And the prices were WAY BETTER than what you would find going into a box box store - dont even want to imagine the quality of those! The sushi is good, anything salmon is top of the line.

Havent been here for a while, returned recently for their poke. YUM! got the regular $12, for 2 proteins (tuna and salmon). As we couldnt decide which tuna to get, we got half of the 2 tuna varieties. And we got the crab imitation, octopus salad (YUM), and seaweed salad.  Also got the large $8 seafood congee which is PACKED with various seafood, halibut, scallop, octopus, shrimps. All so tender, perfectly cooked, and HUGE chunks!  Brilliant dish.  Better than chinese congee i have to say!!

One of my favourite fish markets. I miss getting the newsletters, but pointless now that I live in Calgary. Always good service and the salmon is always great value. I also like how they prep the halibut and their sushi is always on point. Every time Im back in BC I make a point of going here.
Seafood extremely fresh. Love that you can pre-order spot prawns and pickup.

There are a lot of seafood options for you to select. The most surprising thing for me is they have poke! Tried it and love it. So fresh and large portion. The rice a bit soggy to me but overall is pretty good. Definitely recommend

Fresh, and clean. One would think that their price is higher, but i do find it reasonable. If you are getting shellfish like clams, or mussels, they would only pick the live ones, and remove all the dead/ or looks like dead ones for you.

The fish is very good but what is different are the sushi bowls with rice or salad tuna, salmon etc. They are amazing and at a great price. Its something that I havent seen before at a fish store. If I feel like a healthy meal I pop in and take one away.

A wide variety of fresh fish and surprisingly POKE bowls! Expert staff.  Frozen fish locker.  Sushi chef creates small amounts of sushi each day.  NEW to this shop is the addition of POKE bowls prepared fresh for you from a great selection of options.

Had the Halibut cheeks last night. To die for !! Will definately be back to buy more. The jumbo shrimp and fresh halibut I bought last time, fresh and good prices. Wish I could post a photo dinner was so good.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: This is so awesome to hear Barbara - thanks so much for stopping by!

reviews.review_text: My wife and I go here for great oysters that we shuck at home. Delicious and we like the smaller ones. Their Dungeness crab cakes are yummy too.

An absolutely wonderful place to shop. A large selection of fresh, previously frozen and frozen seafood. The staff is courteous and helpful with explaining any off their products. They welcome everyone with a smile and are ready to help you.
I live close to Steveston and the docks.  I still prefer to drive to F.I.S.H   even though its 25 minutes away   everything is great staff are helpful and the poke bar is excellent
Best place in town to get the freshest seafood! Poke bowls are amazing too. always great friendly service too. Highly recommended!
Convenient location for fresh local seafood. The sashimi grade wild sockeye salmon is delish. The staff are always really friendly!
Amazing service and delicious poke bowls! Will definitely be coming back here again!
Great seafood selection: fresh, prepared, frozen. Excellent sushi to go, especially inari pockets filled with a mix of fish, avocado, mayo that tastes like a great Symphony sounds
The owner is the best! High energy happy proud of his store and excited for customers to enjoy the quality products he offers!
Great small shop overall, only shocked when i see the tips option when paying with credit card. It is a fish shop isn t it, not a restaurant.  I am confused.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hi there! Thanks for taking time to review our business. We pride ourselves in providing excellent customer service, and many happy  customers have requested to have an option to allow them to tip! As we take all our customers feedback seriously, we have added this option as well as a No Tip option. We are happy to hear that you enjoyed your visit and we hope to see you again soon!

reviews.review_text: Freshest fish in town and friendly, knowledgable staff. The sablefish is delicious. Marinate in their sake miso sauce and grill. Yum!
I m so glad they have a fish bar here now! Fresh sustainable poke in South Burnaby is now a reality! The staff are friendly and knowledgeable and the food is always prepared fresh! Love it!
Sent them a message on IG with online order issues at 9pm n got a reply within several minutes. Picked up in store and the staff were friendly. Great unique products!
Amazing quality of seafood and they now have a Poke Bowl station where they make the most amazing Poke Bowls. Lots of ingredients and fresh, fresh, fresh!
Anyways great service and a good selection of fresh and frozen seafood. We really enjoy their poke bowls as well!!!
There s a poke bar at the back and it s a hidden gem
Consistently fresh seafood from sustainable sources at fair prices.  Love this place!  Favorites include live sea urchin, smoked sablefish, salmon candy, and the halibut fish cakes.  Yum!
Fresh large and delicious alive oysters
Best onigiri ever! Today was better than before.
The Indian candy is absolutely amazing, as well as the fresh crab. This place is expensive but you get what you pay for, its incredible something so specialized is in such an area!
The hike is not too hard.
Picked up some beautiful mussels for a linguini dish tonight. Also got some nice roll mops, great fish monger selling excellent seafood.
Great selection, fresh and frozen. Excellent customer service
Always something new and yummy. Great service. More then just your average fish monger!
Always a great selection of fresh seafood. Staff are very courteous and helpful.
This is the best seafood store i have ever been to. Great selection of fresh fish and friendly helpful staff.
Went there for the poke bowl. Delicious and large portions. Its just takeout though. No where to sit.
Its my go to poke spot in Vancouver. The fish is so fresh!
Freshest seafood and best poke bowls! Check them out! Its a must!
They have fresh fish and lunch combos. Pretty good.
Very friendly staff, super clean premises, with FRESH, top quality fish and seafood.
Only fresh Ahi in MetroVancouver. Sushi grade and NOT previously frozen. Pricey
Discovered the great poke bowls and the cute employee too late on my last day working in the area.
You can get a wide variety of fresh fishes here, reasonable prices. Only problem is public accessibility
My go-to seafood shop. Good service, quality, pricing. Two thumbs up.
very tasty crabs and good service, I would recommend
Friendly staff, awesome seafood
Fresh seafood and very friendly service. Will go again for sure
Excellent fresh seafood here with knowledgeable staff. I highly recommend the mussels
The only place to go for uni and affordable, generous and delicious poke bowls!
Nothing but really good seafood
Always stop by when in the area.  Fresh and yummy seafood
Great choices of locally sourced seafood. Dont buy seafood anywhere else.
Outstanding quality seafood and really great service.  Will be back for sure.
My favorite place for poke! Generous portions and super fresh!
Great shrimp and friendly customer service.  Ill drive out there again.
Great staff, fresh and delicious fish at a great price!
Great shop for fresh seafood. Recommended if you are in the area.
Fresh right off their own boats. Good variety, identify where its caught.
Cant beat fresh halibut on a hot summers day
Some of the best Poke bowls in town
They have a good Poke bowl
Good poke, a take out only place.
Great fish market and helpful staff!
Excellent place and service.
Good fish
Great place to pick up local seafood
Ordering online is simple and straightforward.
Good selection and friendly service
Excellent salmon.
